subparagraph.content:
relating to private immovable property situated in the receiving State,
                    unless the member of the consular post holds it on behalf of the sending State
                    for the purposes of the consular post;

relating to succession in which the member of the consular post is involved
                    as executor, administrator, heir or legatee as a private person and not on
                    behalf of the sending State;

relating to any professional or commercial activity exercised by the member
                    of the consular post in the receiving State outside his official
                    functions;

arising out of a contract concluded by the member of the consular post in
                    which he did not contract, expressly or impliedly, on behalf of the sending
                    State;
